  "prompt": "What are the top rated Hollywood movies in 2017?",
  "response": "In 2017, several Hollywood movies received critical acclaim and were highly rated by both audiences and critics. Some of the top-rated films from that year include:\n\n1. **Get Out** - Directed by Jordan Peele, this horror film combines social commentary with suspense and was praised for its originality and themes.\n\n2. **Lady Bird** - Greta Gerwig's coming-of-age film about a high school senior navigating her last year in Sacramento received widespread acclaim for its writing and performances.\n\n3. **Dunkirk** - Christopher Nolan\u2019s World War II epic was celebrated for its direction, cinematography, and the immersive nature of its storytelling.\n\n4. **The Shape of Water** - Directed by Guillermo del Toro, this fantasy romance film won several awards, including the Academy Award for Best Picture, and was noted for its unique story and visual style.\n\n5. **Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri** - This dark comedy-drama, directed by Martin McDonagh, received high praise for its performances, particularly by Frances McDormand.\n\n6. **Call Me by Your Name** - A romantic drama directed by Luca Guadagnino, this film was praised for its beautiful storytelling and performances, especially by Timoth\u00e9e Chalamet.\n\n7. **Spider-Man: Homecoming** - This superhero film was well-received for its fresh take on the Spider-Man character and focus on the teenage experiences of Peter Parker.\n\n8. **The Florida Project** - Directed by Sean Baker, this film received acclaim for its portrayal of childhood and lower-income life in America.\n\n9. **Wonder Woman** - Directed by Patty Jenkins, this superhero film was lauded for its direction, performances, especially by Gal Gadot, and its cultural impact.\n\n10. **Blade Runner 2049** - A sequel to the classic, directed by Denis Villeneuve, this film was admired for its visuals, sound design, and philosophical themes.\n\nThese films varied in genre and style, showcasing a diverse range of storytelling in Hollywood for that year.",
